'''Marcos Nicolás Senesi Barón''' (born 10 May 1997) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|AFCBourn}} club [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]. He will join [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 1 July 2026.

==Club career==
===San Lorenzo===
Senesi made his debut for [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]] on 25 September 2016 as a starter in the [[Argentine Primera División]] match against [[Club Atlético Patronato]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Diego|last=Paulich|title=El pibe del Ciclón que le dijo "no" al Villarreal|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/san-lorenzo/senesi-sanlorenzo-villarreal_0_rJ3CeNEcz.html|newspaper=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]]|date=23 March 2018|access-date=7 February 2026|language=es}}</ref> On 16 September 2017, he scored his first and only goal for the club in a 1–0 victory against [[Arsenal de Sarandí]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=San Lorenzo venció a Arsenal con un equipo alternativo|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2017/09/16/con-la-mente-en-la-libertadores-san-lorenzo-enfrenta-a-arsenal/|website=[[Infobae]]|date=16 September 2017|access-date=7 February 2026|language=es}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===
[[File:FC RB Salzburg gegen Feyenoord Rotterdam (Testspiel 2022-07-09) 23.jpg|thumb|Senesi (player with number 4) playing for [[Feyenoord]]]]
On 2 September 2019, Senesi signed a four-year contract with Dutch football club Feyenoord.<ref>{{Cite news|title=El defensor firmó su contrato con el club holandés y en las redes lo presentaron con un video. Mirá.|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-internacional/senesi-firmo-contrato-feyenoord_0_9IBtkA8D5.html|newspaper=Olé|date=2 September 2019|access-date=7 February 2026|language=es}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 22 September 2019, in a 3–3 draw with [[FC Emmen|Emmen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/542859/feyenoord-rotterdam-fc-emmen |title=Emmen 3–3 Feyenoord |website=ESPN |date=22 September 2019 |access-date=13 April 2026}}</ref> On 10 November 2019, he scored his first goal for the club, the winning goal in a 3–2 victory against [[RKC Waalwijk]], heading in a free kick in the 85th minute.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Mikos|last=Gouka|title=Senesi redder van Feyenoord na dramatische start tegen RKC|url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/senesi-redder-van-feyenoord-na-dramatische-start-tegen-rkc~a4a09777/|newspaper=[[Algemeen Dagblad]]|date=10 November 2019|access-date=7 February 2026|language=es}}</ref>

===Bournemouth===
On 8 August 2022, Senesi transferred to Premier League club [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bournemouth complete signing of defender Marcos Senesi from Feyenoord on four-year deal|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11743/12668776/bournemouth-complete-signing-of-defender-marcos-senesi-from-feyenoord-on-four-year-deal|website=[[Sky Sports]]|date=8 August 2022|access-date=7 February 2026}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 13 August 2022, in a 4–0 defeat to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/638215/afc-bournemouth-manchester-city |title=Manchester City 4–0 Bournemouth |website=ESPN |date=13 August 2022 |access-date=13 April 2026}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 11 February 2023, in a 1–1 draw with [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64520929 |title=Bournemouth 1–1 Newcastle United |website=BBC Sport |date=11 February 2023 |access-date=13 April 2026}}</ref> On 15 May 2026, it was confirmed Senesi would leave at the end of his contact.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kinsella |first=Nizaar |date=2026-05-15 |title=Marcos Senesi to leave Bournemouth at end of season |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ckgpyz8p1lgo |access-date= |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Tottenham Hotspur===
On 10 June 2026, it was announced that Senesi will join [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] as a free agent on 1 July, following the expiration of his contract with AFC Bournemouth.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 June 2026 |title= Senesi switch sealed |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/1072863/senesi-switch-sealed |access-date= |website=Tottenham Hotspur |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
Born and raised in Argentina, Senesi is of Italian descent. He was called up to both the [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national teams]], who were about to face each other for the [[2022 Finalissima|Finalissima]] in June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fr12.nl/nieuws/senesi-staat-voor-dilemma-na-oproepen-van-itali-en-argentini|title=Senesi staat voor dilemma na oproepen van Italië en Argentinië|date=13 May 2022|website=FR12.nl|language=nl}}</ref> The same year on 5 June, he chose to represent Argentina, making his debut in a friendly match against [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=¡Abrochado! Marcos Senesi debutó con la camiseta de Argentina y no podrá integrar otro seleccionado: ¿Cómo seguirá su carrera?|url=https://tntsports.com.ar/seleccion/Marcos-Senesi-debut-Seleccion-Argentina-Estonia-20220605-0029.html|website=[[TNT Sports]]|location=Argentina|date=5 June 2022|access-date=7 February 2026|language=es}}</ref>

Senesi was named in the 55-man preliminary squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] on 11 May 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/seleccion-mayor-prelista-de-convocados |title=Selección Mayor: Prelista de convocados |trans-title=Senior National Team: Preliminary squad list |publisher=[[Argentine Football Association]] |date=May 11, 2026 |access-date=May 11, 2026 |archive-date=May 11, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260511125456/https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/seleccion-mayor-prelista-de-convocados |url-status=live }}</ref> A month later, on 11 June, he was called up to the final squad, replacing the injured [[Leonardo Balerdi]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Alcheva |first=Martina |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/amp/world-cup/argentina-confirm-final-26-man-squad-for-the-2026-world-cup-senesi-joins-messis-team-after-balerdi-injury/ |title=Argentina confirm final 26-man squad for the 2026 World Cup: Senesi joins Messi’s team after Balerdi injury |publisher=World Soccer Talk |date=11 June 2026 }}</ref>

